      "message": "As far as I can tell, the core claim justifying this patch (\"Idle multiplexed connections never emit any traffic between protocol events\") is incorrect.\n\nPJSIP already implements a keep-alive mechanism for connections. The key parameters are `PJ_ICE_SESS_KEEP_ALIVE_MIN` and `PJ_ICE_SESS_KEEP_ALIVE_MAX_RAND`, which are set to 20 and 5 respectively in Jami. This means that we expect a STUN keep-alive message to be sent every 20-25 seconds. Empirically, this is exactly what I see when putting a breakpoint in the `ice_keep_alive` function. After a quick search online, it also seems that typical NAT idle timeouts are much longer than the claimed 20-30s when using TCP, so I don\u0027t expect that sending periodic beacons would gain us anything.",
      "revId": "e5c3bf0c5226ed5846cb16ac29bfe281f888a909",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
