      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 390: The timer callback only ignores operation_aborted; any other timer error will still send a beacon and reschedule. While rare, timer errors should not be treated as success because this can keep activity alive after an executor/timer failure and hide the actual problem. Return on any error, and optionally log non-cancellation errors consistently with the rest of the connection code.\n```suggestion\n        if (ec) {\n            if (ec !\u003d asio::error::operation_aborted \u0026\u0026 pimpl.logger_)\n                pimpl.logger_-\u003ewarn(\"[device {}] Beacon interval timer error: {}\", pimpl.deviceId, ec.message());\n            return;\n        }\n```",
